
[1]alarm

   AL'ARM, n.

   1. Any sound, outcry or information intended to give notice of
   approaching danger as, to sound an alarm.

   2. A summon to arms.

   3. Sudden surprise with fear or terror; as, the fire or the enemy
   excited an alarm.

   4. Terror; a sensation excited by an apprehension of danger, from
   whatever cause; as, we felt an alarm at the cry of fire.

   5. In fencing, an appeal or challenge.
